{"ROVE":[{"def":"To draw through an eye or aperture.","pos":""},{"def":"To draw out into falkes; to card, as wool.","pos":""}],"ROVER":[{"def":"A ball which has passed through all the hoops and would go out if it hit the stake but is continued in play; also, the player of such a ball.","pos":""}],"ROVING":[{"def":"The operatin of forming the rove, or slightly twisted sliver or roll of wool or cotton, by means of a machine for the purpose, called a roving frame, or roving machine.","pos":""},{"def":"A roll or sliver of wool or cotton drawn out and slightly twisted; a rove.","pos":""}],"ROVINGLY":[{"def":"In a wandering manner.","pos":""}],"ROVINGNESS":[{"def":"The state of roving.","pos":""}]}